<subSubSection id="C31F652EFF8B7B28FF4F1DEAD8CFFF7B" box="[199,1204,223,248]" pageId="3" pageNumber="207" type="etymology">
<paragraph id="8BBA36A5FF8B7B28FF4F1DEAD8CFFF7B" blockId="3.[151,1436,151,248]" box="[199,1204,223,248]" pageId="3" pageNumber="207">
<emphasis id="B971EAB7FF8B7B28FF4F1DEADD35FF7B" bold="true" box="[199,334,224,248]" pageId="3" pageNumber="207">Etymology.</emphasis>
The name refers to the small cingulum; Greek: minys—small, aulos—a pipe.
</paragraph>
